				<title type="alt">No. 1337. (A.R. No. 386-J of 1896). ON THE SAME PILLAR. A very fine figure of Balarā0ma with the plough in his left hand, the right hanging down and on the head of a standing figure, is inserted in the wall of the shrine with the Āḻvārs. People on the spot say that it is purposely so placed to hide the entrance into the treasure called Śankhanidhi. So is a figure of Srī0nivā0sa found on the corresponding left side hiding the entrance into the Padmanidhi.</title>
